            "chars": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-cad30c79-7fff-855d-6620-5bf748a32c22\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">HT.V-VI.L3</span></em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Tom, and his discovery</span></strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The line looped around Tom&rsquo;s name here appears to be a way of linking this memorandum to the one below about &ldquo;Sleary&rsquo;s Horsemanship and Sissy&rsquo;s father,&rdquo; as Tom&rsquo;s eventual fate&ndash;fleeing Coketown after his guilt is discovered, and then escaping abroad&ndash;is accomplished through Sleary&rsquo;s circus. These two items are linked again on the right-hand side in the notes for chapter 35: &ldquo;Find [Tom] with travelling riders and so work round Sissy&rsquo;s own story&rdquo; (see <em>HT.V-VI.R13</em>).</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"
